5cus C 183 D 183

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between two units of Receptor tyrosine-protein kinase erbB-3 at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Receptor tyrosine-protein kinase erbB-3 at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
